<subSubSection id="3796656070D9FF3FFF23EC9F8B19FBC7" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7F3336EB70D9FF3FFF23EC9F8B19FBC7" blockId="167.[151,1436,678,1027]" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFF23EC9F8B44FD26" bold="true" box="[199,335,714,739]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
The condition of the only known specimen of this species is so poor that discussions of its morphology are limited to the most general and vague characterisation. 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D9FF3FFC6EECBB8E3CFCC3" author="Wilson, E. O." box="[906,1079,750,774]" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" pagination="205 - 216" refId="ref113292" refString="Wilson, E. O. (1985 a) Ants from the Cretaceous and Eocene amber of North America. Psyche, 92, 205 - 216." type="journal article" year="1985">Wilson (1985a)</bibRefCitation>
notes that the species possesses fewer mandibular teeth than New World species then placed in 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D9FF3FFCB2ED4689ECFCEE" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[854,999,787,811]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFCB2ED4689ECFCEE" box="[854,999,787,811]" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(now placed in 
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFB7DED468F2EFCEE" box="[1177,1317,787,811]" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">Linepethima</emphasis>
). He compares the mandibles with those of extant Australian species, finding them similar to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D9FF3FFBBDED628EB1FC8B" box="[1113,1210,822,846]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calvus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFBBDED628EB1FC8B" box="[1113,1210,822,846]" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">I. calvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D9FF3FFB17ED628F7EFC8B" baseAuthorityName="Lowne" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1267,1397,822,846]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoniger">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFB17ED628F7EFC8B" box="[1267,1397,822,846]" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">I. rufoniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as what is now 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D9FF3FFE65ED0E8847FCB6" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[385,588,859,883]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Philidris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordatus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFE65ED0E8847FCB6" box="[385,588,859,883]" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">Philidris cordatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Essentially no other details are provided. With so little information available it is impossible to support a specific generic placement of this taxon, and it is retained here as 
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFB1DED2A8F9EFC53" box="[1273,1429,894,918]" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">incertae sedis</emphasis>
, acknowledging that this placement in 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D9FF3FFDB0EDF688EEFC7E" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[596,741,931,955]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFDB0EDF688EEFC7E" box="[596,741,931,955]" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unsupported and likely to be incorrect based on biogeographic considerations and the great age difference between this species and the origins of modern members of 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D9FF3FFA92ED928B00FBC6" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="167" pageNumber="168" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D9FF3FFA92ED928B00FBC6" italics="true" pageId="167" pageNumber="168">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
